          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### Email Security (Microsoft Defender for Office 365)\nMail-borne threats across the full MDO telemetry set: EmailEvents (verdicts and delivery), EmailUrlInfo (weaponized URLs), EmailAttachmentInfo (malicious files and hashes), EmailPostDeliveryEvents (ZAP remediation), and UrlClickEvents (Safe Links clicks). The tiles, trends and grids below surface what was blocked versus delivered, the senders and domains behind it, the URLs and attachments embedded in mail, and post-delivery clean-up, classic initial-access and credential-harvesting tradecraft the SOC must triage fast.\n\nNote: this workbook reads the Log Analytics / Sentinel workspace. The richest threat verdicts (ThreatTypes, DetectionMethods) populate fully when opened in the unified Microsoft Defender portal; here the panels are built to also light up from delivery action, quarantine location, bulk-complaint level, and the always-populated URL, attachment, ZAP and click tables.",
